            <div class="Facts">
                <h3>What is?</h3>
                <p>  
                    Rawon is a rich and flavorful Indonesian beef soup, renowned for its dark color and intense taste. 
                    Made with a blend of aromatic spices such as galangal, lemongrass, ginger, and candlenuts, Rawon boasts a 
                    distinctively earthy and savory flavor profile. The key ingredient, beef, is simmered until tender in this 
                    fragrant broth, infused with the deep hue of keluak nuts, which also adds a unique bitterness to the dish. 
                    Rawon is typically served with rice, bean sprouts, and fried shallots, with shrimp crackers and a side of 
                    "Sambal Rawon" for added spice. It's a beloved dish in Indonesian cuisine, cherished for its comforting warmth 
                    and bold flavors.
                </p>
