            <div class="Instructions">
                <h3>Instructions</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Blend all the pasta ingredients in a blender or food processor until smooth. Add a little oil if needed to aid the blending process.</li>
                    <li>Boil 2 liters of water in a deep pot. Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and add the beef. Cook until tender. If necessary, drain and discard any excess fat.</li>
                    <li>Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a skillet. SautÃ© the pasta, lemongrass, galangal, and kaffir lime leaves until the paste is cooked and fragrant.</li>
                    <li>Transfer the pasta to the pot with the cooked beef. Add pepper, palm sugar, and salt. Adjust the seasoning.</li>
                    <li>If the beef is cooked, add chopped spring onions.</li>
                    <li>Prepare the soup in separate serving bowls, garnished with bean sprouts and fried shallots.</li>
                    <li>Serve with shrimp crackers and "Sambal Rawon" if desired. Many Indonesians enjoy Rawon with boiled salted duck eggs as a condiment.</li>
